	abstract = {The development of digital technology has driven the need for a more transparent, efficient, and accurate tax audit system. The traditional tax audit process often faces challenges, including delays in data verification, the risk of financial statement manipulation, and a lack of integration among taxpayers, tax consultants, and tax authorities. This study aims to develop a blockchain implementation model in an Automated and Real-Time Tax Audit system that can be utilized by tax consultants to improve audit efficiency and accuracy. Simulation results with Hyperledger Fabric show that consortium members must validate tax-related transactions before they are stored on the blockchain. Therefore, the information generated from the blockchain-based tax audit system is guaranteed to be transparent and valid. This system can also be used by tax consultants to conduct continuous tax compliance analysis without the need for complex manual verification processes. Thus, applying blockchain to automated, real-time tax audits can be an innovative solution to improve the accountability and effectiveness of tax processes in the digital era. © 2025 IEEE.},
